HTML Audio and Video Elements
HTML provides two elements for embedding multimedia content: audio and video. These elements allow you to add audio and video content to your web pages.

HTML Audio Element
The audio element is used to embed audio content in a web page. You can specify the source of the audio file using the src attribute.


<audio controls>
  <source src="audio.mp3" type="audio/mp3">
  Your browser does not support the audio element.
</audio>


Attributes of Audio Element
1. controls: Displays audio controls, such as play, pause, and volume.
2. autoplay: Automatically plays the audio when the page loads.
3. loop: Loops the audio playback.

HTML Video Element
The video element is used to embed video content in a web page. You can specify the source of the video file using the src attribute.


<video width="640" height="480" controls>
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  Your browser does not support the video element.
</video>


Attributes of Video Element
1. controls: Displays video controls, such as play, pause, and volume.
2. autoplay: Automatically plays the video when the page loads.
3. loop: Loops the video playback.
4. width and height: Specifies the width and height of the video player.

Real-time Examples
1. Embedding an audio file: You can use the audio element to embed an audio file on your web page.

<audio controls>
  <source src="song.mp3" type="audio/mp3">
  Your browser does not support the audio element.
</audio>


2. Embedding a video file: You can use the video element to embed a video file on your web page.

<video width="640" height="480" controls>
  <source src="movie.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  Your browser does not support the video element.
</video>


CSS Styling
You can style the audio and video elements using CSS. For example, you can change the width and height of the video player.


video {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}


Questions and Answers
1. *Q: What is the purpose of the audio element?*
    - A: The audio element is used to embed audio content in a web page.

2. *Q: What is the purpose of the video element?*
    - A: The video element is used to embed video content in a web page.

3. Q: How do you specify the source of an audio or video file?
    - A: You can specify the source of an audio or video file using the src attribute.

4. *Q: What are the benefits of using the audio and video elements?*
    - A: The audio and video elements allow you to embed multimedia content in a web page, enhancing the user experience and providing a more engaging and interactive experience.

5. *Q: Can you style the audio and video elements using CSS?*
    - A: Yes, you can style the audio and video elements using CSS, such as changing the width and height of the video player.